body:
> I've tested this and it works great. I think we need to resolve this question: [#16688 (comment)](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/16688#issuecomment-543388763) before merging this PR. It seems reasonable to me to change logging back to using a macro for the reasons you suggest. Adding a `GetHash()` call to every validation interface call, even when logging is disabled, seems a shame. I'd be happy to review a PR that does that.

@jnewbery Will do.

@MarcoFalke I'm not sure I follow the part about "unnecessary branches are not analyzed" in #14209. If I were to make `LogPrint` (but not `LogPrintf`) a macro again, will I need to define it conditionally based on `USE_COVERAGE` as was done in c8914b9?

